.ssh/authorized_keys

# What file contains the RSA keys of systems 
# that are authorized to connect via SSH?

# RSA (Rivest–Shamir–Adleman)加密算法 is one of the first public-key cryptosystems 
# and is widely used for secure data transmission.

# ssh-keygen to generate the key
# This procedure has generated an RSA SSH key pair, 
# located in the .ssh hidden directory within root. 
# ssh-copy-id username@remote_host transfer your public key
# ssh username@remote_host login
# mkdir -p ~/.ssh
# https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/ssh-essentials-working-with-ssh-servers-clients-and-keys